<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,506,1143]" pageId="18" pageNumber="491">
Notes. This species was described based on one male and one female specimen deposited in the USNM collection. A male cotype is here designated as 
<typeStatus box="[692,795,1046,1071]" pageId="18" pageNumber="491">lectotype</typeStatus>
to fix the identity of the species. This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Melichar" authorityYear="1923" box="[151,310,1083,1107]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Makilingia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis box="[151,310,1083,1107]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="491">M. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in having only a narrow yellow longitudinal stripe along the forewing commissure rather than a pair of large transcommissural yellow spots.
</paragraph>
